      "span_text": "As well as likelihood of escape, proximity to a place of safety can also influence whether animals choose to adopt a strategy of TI or attempt to flee from a predator. [CITATION_1] demonstrated in a laboratory that rabbits (Oryctolagus cuniculus) decreased the duration of TI as proximity to a human decreased or as proximity to their home cage increased."
